1
00:00:05,266 --> 00:00:06,366
What I want?

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,600
And if I want to act in a series,

3
00:00:09,133 --> 00:00:10,766
you'd let me, right?

4
00:00:11,066 --> 00:00:13,100
I want you to do what you love.

5
00:00:13,466 --> 00:00:14,900
Bangkok is just so comfy.

6
00:00:15,466 --> 00:00:16,600
Why would she come back?

7
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,000
Tor Prakai.

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,316
Here for the casting.

9
00:00:19,316 --> 00:00:19,816
Whoa!

10
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:25,266
Oops, sorry!

11
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:26,500
Oh, P'Phet!

12
00:00:26,866 --> 00:00:27,666
Where have you been?

13
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:30,466
Hello.

14
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:34,166
I'm Tor Prakai's boyfriend.

15
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,700
Don't tell me you're...

16
00:00:47,266 --> 00:00:48,133
Khun 9T?

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:51,516
Yes, I'm Nine Theeraphat.

18
00:00:52,624 --> 00:00:54,097
Nice to meet you.

19
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,327
Nine!

20
00:01:11,327 --> 00:01:12,997
I'm your fan.

21
00:01:12,997 --> 00:01:14,400
I'd love a photo with you.

22
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:15,666
Of course.

23
00:01:21,966 --> 00:01:22,766
Thank you.

24
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:26,600
Whoa.

25
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:28,333
He's so famous.

26
00:01:29,533 --> 00:01:30,333
Totally.

27
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:32,466
Everyone knows me.

28
00:01:33,566 --> 00:01:34,666
Except for you.

29
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,166
Who could remember every actor in the country?

30
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,918
Do you remember every Korean star's face?

31
00:01:41,918 --> 00:01:42,700
Hmm.

32
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,300
Got an answer for everything, huh?

33
00:01:52,666 --> 00:01:53,466
This place is delicious.

34
00:01:53,766 --> 00:01:55,366
Should bring P'Phet back.

35
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,200
Gonna bookmark it.

36
00:02:00,966 --> 00:02:01,559
Hey.

37
00:02:01,928 --> 00:02:02,966
Are you done eating?

38
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:05,666
Why?

39
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:07,866
I told you I'd drop you off.

40
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:12,733
Do you know the way?

41
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:15,933
Google Maps exists, you know.

42
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,400
Is it free?

43
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,000
Yeah.

44
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:23,666
I don't want money.

45
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,500
But I want...

46
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,600
Oops.

47
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,400
I'll tell the press!

48
00:02:34,133 --> 00:02:34,933
You talk too much.

49
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,866
Aren't you in a hurry?

50
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:43,600
Gosh, will I make it back in time?

51
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,733
If you're in a rush, let's go.

52
00:02:47,466 --> 00:02:50,566
Let's spend time together so we won't be awkward at work.

53
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:52,073
What work?

54
00:02:52,535 --> 00:02:54,000
The results aren't even out.

55
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,466
Come on, if you fail,

56
00:02:57,066 --> 00:02:58,866
I'll hire you as a crew member.

57
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:00,700
No way.

58
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,400
If I fail this one, I'll try another.

59
00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:05,172
Whatever.

60
00:03:06,049 --> 00:03:07,325
With a face like mine,

61
00:03:07,556 --> 00:03:08,415
I'm bound to get a role.

62
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:12,700
Fine.

63
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,500
Check, please.

64
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,133
Calculating now.

65
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:19,003
Sure.

66
00:03:22,466 --> 00:03:22,966
Scan here, please.

67
00:03:22,966 --> 00:03:23,766
Thank you.

68
00:03:36,666 --> 00:03:38,533
You said you're my brother's boyfriend?

69
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:41,700
Yes.

70
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,333
How did they meet?

71
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:45,700
Where?

72
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:46,533
Who are you?

73
00:03:46,533 --> 00:03:47,466
And what do you do for a living?

74
00:03:50,566 --> 00:03:51,600
Calm down.

75
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:57,416
Well...

76
00:03:58,617 --> 00:03:59,533
It's like...

77
00:03:59,533 --> 00:04:01,133
Wait a second.

78
00:04:06,008 --> 00:04:06,720
Hi.

79
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:09,566
almost there.

80
00:04:11,466 --> 00:04:12,266
see you.

81
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,548
Hey, Bae.

82
00:04:18,148 --> 00:04:19,581
I'll see you later.

83
00:04:20,874 --> 00:04:21,968
Don't be naughty.

84
00:04:22,475 --> 00:04:23,495
And this...

85
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,446
is what you forgot.

86
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:37,086
Uh, in that case...

87
00:04:37,086 --> 00:04:40,807
Goodbye, everyone. Next time, we'll talk more.

88
00:04:41,176 --> 00:04:43,035
I'll take my leave now.

89
00:04:55,366 --> 00:04:56,166
Hey!

90
00:04:56,766 --> 00:04:57,666
Is he a star?

91
00:04:58,800 --> 00:04:59,600
Right?

92
00:05:00,933 --> 00:05:01,766
What's his name?

93
00:05:03,966 --> 00:05:04,520
Nine.

94
00:05:04,889 --> 00:05:06,300
The BL actor.

95
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:07,900
huh?

96
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:08,766
(Pleng Chai) A BL series?
(Lynchee) Let me search.

97
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,133
So familiar.

98
00:05:12,666 --> 00:05:13,838
Here it is.

99
00:05:14,115 --> 00:05:15,601
Nine Theeraphat.

100
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:17,661
Actor in a series...

101
00:05:18,585 --> 00:05:19,917
...with 100 million views.

102
00:05:21,626 --> 00:05:24,076
Oops, I should've asked for a photo.

103
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,798
You're hopeless.

104
00:05:25,798 --> 00:05:27,823
YOU... have a superstar boyfriend?

105
00:05:37,366 --> 00:05:38,166
Guy.

106
00:05:38,266 --> 00:05:39,883
Oh, P'Phet!

107
00:05:39,883 --> 00:05:43,598
Guy's back safe and sound, see?

108
00:05:44,245 --> 00:05:46,813
Let's talk later, just calm down.

109
00:05:48,066 --> 00:05:48,597
Guy.

110
00:05:48,597 --> 00:05:49,366
P'Phet.

111
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,733
We have plenty of time to talk.

112
00:05:52,966 --> 00:05:54,066
Calm down.

113
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:57,466
Calm down, okay?

114
00:06:00,766 --> 00:06:01,533
Guy.

115
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:04,696
Let's go help with the bags instead.

116
00:06:04,696 --> 00:06:07,538
Look at all this luggage.

117
00:06:07,538 --> 00:06:09,091
Guy, go help me grab the bags, hurry.

118
00:06:09,091 --> 00:06:10,400
Everyone, help out.

119
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:10,923
Yes.

120
00:06:10,923 --> 00:06:13,466
Hurry up and grab the bags.

121
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:14,666
Pleng.

122
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,166
huh?

123
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:15,966
Get down from that chair.

124
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:17,333
Help with the bags.

125
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:18,600
How did they meet?

126
00:06:18,733 --> 00:06:20,249
(Ploy Ying) Move it, move it!
(Lynchee) P'Nine!

127
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,220
Let's go!

128
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:22,467
Move it!

129
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,600
Where did you meet him?

130
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,700
Tell me everything.

131
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,325
(Lynchee) Hurry!
(Pleng Chai) Lynchee!

132
00:06:28,325 --> 00:06:29,666
(Lynchee) Oops, I forgot.
(Pleng Chai) Forgot the bag.

133
00:06:29,866 --> 00:06:30,666
Thank you.

134
00:07:56,729 --> 00:07:58,261
Sorry, Guy.
Right now, we have two roles available.

135
00:07:58,261 --> 00:08:00,000
The lead and the second lead.
The producer wants another casting call.

136
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,400
But you have to compete with someone else...
to see who fits which role.

137
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,938
Are you available, Guy?
I'll come pick you up.

138
00:08:02,938 --> 00:08:04,500
Sure, I'll share my location.

139
00:08:06,947 --> 00:08:07,798
Where are you going?

140
00:08:07,798 --> 00:08:08,828
I'm hungry. Out getting food.

141
00:08:08,828 --> 00:08:09,813
Which shop? I'll come find you.

142
00:08:09,813 --> 00:08:10,659
No need.

143
00:08:11,536 --> 00:08:13,046
I'm far from the hotel, almost done too.
Don't come. You'll just get lost again.

144
00:08:13,046 --> 00:08:13,997
Never lost! Bring me some food then.

145
00:08:13,997 --> 00:08:14,857
Why eat? You'll get fat.

146
00:08:14,857 --> 00:08:16,739
I won't. I'm not getting fat like you.

147
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,400
Hello. Please introduce yourself.

148
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:22,771
Hello.

149
00:08:24,249 --> 00:08:26,928
I'm Jomtien, a Likay hero.

150
00:08:27,251 --> 00:08:30,000
I'm so happy to be casting for this series.

151
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:34,300
Today, I have an actor...
I'd like you to try a partner scene with.

152
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,733
Do you know Nine?

153
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,200
Yes, I do.

154
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:42,333
And today, I have another candidate.

155
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,566
His name is Tor Prakai.

156
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:48,300
Tor Prakai is also a Likay hero like you.

157
00:08:48,533 --> 00:08:49,333
Do you know each other?

158
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:52,133
I know him very well.

159
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:54,700
Oh, Khun Nine!

160
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:57,466
Hello.

161
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,012
Hello, Khun Nine.

162
00:08:59,012 --> 00:09:01,341
I must apologize, Khun Nine.

163
00:09:01,341 --> 00:09:03,869
I have a Likay performance tonight...

164
00:09:03,869 --> 00:09:06,133
so I had to ask you to come here instead.

165
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:07,600
It's no problem at all.

166
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,655
We have two roles open right now.

167
00:09:11,655 --> 00:09:14,768
The lead role, opposite Nine.

168
00:09:14,768 --> 00:09:20,126
And the second lead, who has a crush
on Nine but ends up heartbroken.

169
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:21,127
So...

170
00:09:21,127 --> 00:09:26,752
I'd like to try one more casting
that see who is suited for a role

171
00:09:26,752 --> 00:09:27,400
better than another.

172
00:09:27,933 --> 00:09:30,166
Excuse me.

173
00:09:30,166 --> 00:09:30,666
Excu... .

174
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,800
P'Jom.

175
00:09:33,766 --> 00:09:34,566
Guy.

176
00:09:34,933 --> 00:09:35,733
Okay.

177
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:37,166
We're all here.

178
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:41,600
Let's start with Nine and Jomtien first.

179
00:09:42,133 --> 00:09:44,333
Guy, please wait outside for now.

180
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,933
You're up next.

181
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,400
Ready?

182
00:09:49,766 --> 00:09:50,566
Yes.

183
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:51,933
Okay.

184
00:09:52,366 --> 00:09:53,166
Ready?

185
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:56,133
And...

186
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,300
Action!

187
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,100
Give me your hand.

188
00:10:06,566 --> 00:10:07,866
Whoever I give my Gear to...

189
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,700
is the person I trust with my heart.

190
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:13,366
Take good care of it.

191
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:16,966
You gave it to me.

192
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,966
I'm not giving it back.

193
00:10:38,266 --> 00:10:39,585
And this...

194
00:10:40,739 --> 00:10:41,966
is for you.

195
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,000
A fair trade.

196
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:54,800
Cut!

197
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:56,800
That was great.

198
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,300
Thank you.

199
00:10:58,500 --> 00:11:00,366
Jomtien, you can step out for now.

200
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:01,133
Sure.

201
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:03,500
And now it's Guy's turn.

202
00:11:05,533 --> 00:11:06,458
Thank you.

203
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:06,958
Yes.

204
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,333
Come in, Guy.

205
00:11:15,266 --> 00:11:16,533
Are you okay, Guy?

206
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,133
Ready?

207
00:11:18,933 --> 00:11:19,733
Are you ready?

208
00:11:21,466 --> 00:11:22,496
Okay.

209
00:11:22,496 --> 00:11:23,366
Are you both ready?

210
00:11:23,366 --> 00:11:23,866
Ready.

211
00:11:23,866 --> 00:11:24,866
Let's begin.

212
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,366
And... action!

213
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,227
Whoever I give my Gear to...

214
00:11:42,443 --> 00:11:45,008
is the person I trust with my heart.

215
00:11:48,379 --> 00:11:48,879
Here, take it.

216
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:57,346
It's yours.

217
00:11:58,454 --> 00:12:00,056
So don't make it someone else's burden.

218
00:12:01,626 --> 00:12:02,634
Besides...

219
00:12:03,465 --> 00:12:04,228
I'm here to study,

220
00:12:04,597 --> 00:12:06,035
not to find a husband.

221
00:12:09,266 --> 00:12:10,066
Oh my!

222
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,566
Uh... Guy?

223
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:14,300
Why did you play it like that?

224
00:12:18,466 --> 00:12:19,469
Oh, well...

225
00:12:21,039 --> 00:12:22,812
Once I knew I'd be in this series,

226
00:12:22,812 --> 00:12:24,450
I went and read the novel.

227
00:12:24,681 --> 00:12:25,878
So I thought...

228
00:12:26,432 --> 00:12:27,745
the lead character...

229
00:12:27,745 --> 00:12:29,229
is more of a nerd.

230
00:12:29,737 --> 00:12:31,308
He doesn't care about romance.

231
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:36,383
Wow, so impressive. You really studied the source material.

232
00:12:36,383 --> 00:12:37,536
Yes, very good.

233
00:12:38,136 --> 00:12:40,550
Good, good.

234
00:12:58,606 --> 00:13:01,223
I won't. I'm not getting fat like you.

235
00:13:01,223 --> 00:13:03,006
Are you really eating? It's been ages.

236
00:13:03,006 --> 00:13:04,221
I'm on my way back.

237
00:13:04,221 --> 00:13:04,835
No, it's nothing.

238
00:13:04,835 --> 00:13:06,837
You're afraid of ghosts, right? Just admit it.

239
00:13:06,837 --> 00:13:08,283
I'm not scared!

240
00:13:08,283 --> 00:13:11,227
Gonna play games. Too lazy to talk.

241
00:13:16,602 --> 00:13:17,949
Casting day atmosphere #HomeOfHearts #EngineeringChaos

242
00:13:17,949 --> 00:13:19,437
Who will be part of the series?
Follow the results tomorrow.

243
00:13:20,222 --> 00:13:21,210
Thank you so much for today, Guy.

244
00:13:21,210 --> 00:13:22,841
Good luck tomorrow.

245
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:41,138
Guy!

246
00:13:41,877 --> 00:13:43,672
So, where did you actually go today?

247
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:48,266
Oh, keeping quiet?

248
00:13:51,766 --> 00:13:52,566
What are you doing?

249
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:54,500
Talking to your boyfriend?

250
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,400
He turned off his phone.

251
00:14:01,066 --> 00:14:01,866
huh?

252
00:14:02,766 --> 00:14:03,696
You're really...

253
00:14:04,112 --> 00:14:05,577
...acting so suspicious.

254
00:14:05,933 --> 00:14:07,533
I'm keeping my eye on you.

255
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,800
huh.

256
00:14:09,866 --> 00:14:11,366
No need to keep an eye on me.

257
00:14:12,566 --> 00:14:13,466
Because I've got...

258
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:16,789
a film

259
00:14:17,851 --> 00:14:18,351
blocking

260
00:14:19,321 --> 00:14:20,000
meddling eyes.

261
00:14:26,366 --> 00:14:27,200
Block who?

262
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,100
Block me?

263
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,118
Guy, you jerk!

264
00:14:34,672 --> 00:14:37,086
Did you just insult me? Let me see what you're doing.

265
00:14:37,086 --> 00:14:38,794
Let me see.

266
00:14:38,794 --> 00:14:39,820
Let me see!

267
00:14:47,966 --> 00:14:49,166
Watch your back.

268
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:52,500
I'm done with you.

269
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,533
Oh, Guy...

270
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,900
I wonder how you're doing.

271
00:15:23,266 --> 00:15:25,200
Did you accidentally let P'Phet find out?

272
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,362
Hey, Guy!

273
00:15:33,932 --> 00:15:35,656
Hey, wake up!

274
00:15:35,887 --> 00:15:36,827
Look at this!

275
00:15:38,113 --> 00:15:38,753
Wake up!

276
00:15:38,984 --> 00:15:39,796
Look at this first.

277
00:15:41,228 --> 00:15:41,989
What is it?

278
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,427
I just dreamed I had garlands all over my neck.

279
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:47,873
Look at this first.

280
00:15:49,674 --> 00:15:51,063
Pro Football Betting.
Deposit / Withdraw / Transfer.

281
00:15:51,063 --> 00:15:53,155
All-in-one site.
(Pong) Maybe he just looks like him, man.

282
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,300
Yeah.

283
00:15:59,866 --> 00:16:00,666
Yeah, right.

284
00:16:01,966 --> 00:16:03,100
He just looks like him.

285
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,133
Startled for nothing.

286
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,500
Can we sleep now? I'm sleepy.

287
00:17:02,133 --> 00:17:03,366
I told you already.

288
00:17:04,566 --> 00:17:06,500
That I want to repay you.

289
00:17:14,266 --> 00:17:15,401
I'm going.

290
00:17:15,632 --> 00:17:17,486
And I'll make it happen.

291
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:20,492
And if I ever get on TV one day,

292
00:17:21,231 --> 00:17:23,185
I'll make Petchprakai Likay Troupe...

293
00:17:23,508 --> 00:17:26,549
...famous nationwide.

294
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,066
Don't you think it's weird?

295
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,400
That Guy has a movie star boyfriend?

296
00:18:26,766 --> 00:18:27,674
Someone like him?

297
00:18:27,905 --> 00:18:28,405
Why?

298
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,333
What's wrong with Guy's face?

299
00:18:32,966 --> 00:18:35,500
Our brother is quite handsome.

300
00:18:35,666 --> 00:18:36,466
Whoa!

301
00:18:38,966 --> 00:18:40,066
You call this handsome?

302
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:40,900
Yeah, why?

303
00:18:40,900 --> 00:18:42,166
Not even as good as Pleng's snot. Look.

304
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,466
Eww, gross.

305
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,600
Do you know how to spell manners?

306
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:52,200
M-A-N...

307
00:18:53,766 --> 00:18:54,966
N-E-R...

308
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,300
S!

309
00:18:58,126 --> 00:18:58,952
Hey!

310
00:19:00,866 --> 00:19:01,443
Whoa!

311
00:19:01,443 --> 00:19:02,332
Isn't that right?

312
00:19:02,332 --> 00:19:02,866
No.

313
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,966
Let me re-teach you Thai.

314
00:19:06,866 --> 00:19:07,569
Mistakes happen.

315
00:19:07,569 --> 00:19:08,830
Casting results #EngineeringChaos

316
00:19:21,366 --> 00:19:22,200
What's wrong with her?

317
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,000
Where is she going?

318
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,000
What's wrong with Ploy?

319
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:30,933
I passed.

320
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,666
I passed!

321
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:33,933
Passed what?

322
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:36,535
The series I auditioned for.

323
00:19:36,866 --> 00:19:37,666
huh?

324
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,866
Congrats, P'Ploy!

325
00:19:41,266 --> 00:19:42,138
Let me see.

326
00:19:42,138 --> 00:19:42,733
Here.

327
00:19:57,510 --> 00:19:59,008
Announcement post: Finalists for Engineering Chaos.

328
00:19:59,008 --> 00:19:59,785
Tor Prakai.

329
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:00,900
Whoa!

330
00:20:05,966 --> 00:20:06,766
Hello.

331
00:20:07,466 --> 00:20:10,666
Congrats, rookie actor.

332
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:13,599
You.

333
00:20:14,384 --> 00:20:15,769
Did I really get it?

334
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,241
Of course.

335
00:20:17,241 --> 00:20:19,049
But it's not because of me.

336
00:20:19,049 --> 00:20:20,766
It's because you're the right fit.

337
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:22,590
Thank you.

338
00:20:23,467 --> 00:20:25,224
I'll do my best.

339
00:20:25,547 --> 00:20:27,424
I won't let anyone down.

340
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,166
See you at the workshop.

341
00:20:30,566 --> 00:20:32,366
Read the script carefully this time.

342
00:20:32,866 --> 00:20:33,933
I won't help you next time.

343
00:20:34,966 --> 00:20:35,766
Sure.

344
00:21:42,422 --> 00:21:44,636
Ploy passed.

345
00:21:44,959 --> 00:21:47,377
When are you free to sign the contract?

346
00:21:58,876 --> 00:21:59,967
P'Phet.

347
00:22:02,045 --> 00:22:03,067
Yeah?

348
00:22:04,222 --> 00:22:05,502
I think you should know about this.

349
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:23,900
huh?

350
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:25,400
You're here?

351
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,066
You troublemaker.

352
00:22:28,066 --> 00:22:28,866
What?

353
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:36,933
You know, right?

354
00:22:37,866 --> 00:22:39,000
That secrets...

355
00:22:40,466 --> 00:22:41,893
...don't stay hidden forever.

356
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:44,700
I know.

357
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,733
Like when you took money from P'Ploy for games.

358
00:22:47,966 --> 00:22:48,766
I even knew that.

359
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:55,381
Keep talking.

360
00:22:55,658 --> 00:22:57,760
Mine was just a small thing.

361
00:22:58,268 --> 00:22:59,454
But yours...

362
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:09,900
Are you chuunibyou or what?

363
00:23:10,466 --> 00:23:11,800
Have you been watching too much anime?

364
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:13,494
huh?

365
00:23:13,494 --> 00:23:14,393
Smartmouth.

366
00:23:14,393 --> 00:23:14,933
Guy.

367
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:22,366
Ploy.

368
00:23:22,566 --> 00:23:23,366
Yes?

369
00:23:23,366 --> 00:23:25,266
Do you know Guy went for a series casting?

370
00:23:30,582 --> 00:23:31,382
Well...

371
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:37,400
P'Phet.

372
00:23:40,333 --> 00:23:41,840
Don't blame P'Ploy.

373
00:23:42,532 --> 00:23:43,296
About this...

374
00:23:45,282 --> 00:23:46,838
I made the decision myself.

375
00:23:47,933 --> 00:23:48,966
You decided yourself?

376
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,366
And how many times have you decided yourself?

377
00:23:54,666 --> 00:23:55,466
Why?

378
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,566
Is being with Petchprakai that bad?

379
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:00,066
Even though I gave you everything.

380
00:24:00,166 --> 00:24:01,966
I taught you to sing, dance, and everything.

381
00:24:01,966 --> 00:24:03,333
So you could be a great Likay hero.

382
00:24:03,333 --> 00:24:04,466
But I didn't want to be!

383
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:14,066
What I wanted you to do...

384
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,300
...did you ever ask if I wanted to do it?

385
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,333
Did you ever care?

386
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:26,000
What I like?

387
00:24:26,766 --> 00:24:27,566
What I don't?

388
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,766
Or does P'Phet only care about himself?

389
00:24:35,266 --> 00:24:36,533
Why do you think that way?

390
00:24:39,733 --> 00:24:41,600
Did your boyfriend teach you to think like this?

391
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:51,533
Let me tell you something.

392
00:24:53,766 --> 00:24:55,166
Nine isn't my boyfriend.

393
00:24:58,766 --> 00:25:00,000
But he helped me...

394
00:25:01,293 --> 00:25:03,935
...when I needed help.

395
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,300
Which is something...

396
00:25:10,166 --> 00:25:12,133
...I never got from P'Phet.

397
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,600
If it's so great,

398
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,600
if it's that good, then go live with him!

399
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:21,400
You don't want to be with Petchprakai anyway.

400
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:35,566
Are you kicking me out...

401
00:25:38,533 --> 00:25:40,400
...because if I don't perform Likay,

402
00:25:41,866 --> 00:25:43,766
I'm useless to you, right?

403
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:52,700
Fine.

404
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:54,466
Then I'm leaving.

405
00:26:02,666 --> 00:26:03,612
Guy! Guy!

406
00:26:03,612 --> 00:26:04,900
Let it go for now, P'Phet.

407
00:26:05,933 --> 00:26:07,133
Let Guy go.

408
00:26:07,666 --> 00:26:09,166
Calm down first, then we'll talk.

409
00:26:09,333 --> 00:26:10,333
And you too, Ploy.

410
00:26:12,266 --> 00:26:14,400
You knew everything but didn't tell me.

411
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:16,066
That's why this happened.

412
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:17,300
Listen.

413
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:20,966
Is it all my fault?

414
00:26:24,133 --> 00:26:26,923
Blaming others is easier than blaming yourself, right?

415
00:26:28,401 --> 00:26:29,711
I know...

416
00:26:30,727 --> 00:26:31,769
...that one day...

417
00:26:32,646 --> 00:26:34,551
...you'll regret what you said.

418
00:26:36,900 --> 00:26:38,900
Talk to me once you've come to your senses.

419
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:42,314
Pleng.

420
00:26:42,545 --> 00:26:44,164
Stay here if you want.

421
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,300
Help P'Phet with whatever you can.

422
00:26:47,466 --> 00:26:48,866
I'm heading back for now.

423
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,200
P'Ploy!

424
00:26:58,766 --> 00:26:59,866
P'Phet, calm down.

425
00:27:14,700 --> 00:27:15,500
What on earth?

426
00:27:27,466 --> 00:27:28,422
What's wrong?

427
00:27:28,699 --> 00:27:30,000
Why are you sitting here alone?

428
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:32,266
Oh, Lynchee.

429
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:36,161
So...

430
00:27:36,392 --> 00:27:38,831
Were you the one who told P'Phet about Tor Prakai?

431
00:27:42,933 --> 00:27:43,966
Yeah, so what?

432
00:27:45,533 --> 00:27:48,166
I just thought P'Phet should know, right?

433
00:27:49,133 --> 00:27:50,933
But I didn't think it would be this big a deal.

434
00:27:53,966 --> 00:27:55,366
Do you think if you hadn't told him,

435
00:27:55,566 --> 00:27:56,800
it would be a smaller issue?

436
00:27:58,266 --> 00:28:00,166
Tor Prakai isn't acting in a student film.

437
00:28:00,733 --> 00:28:01,933
He's in a BL series.

438
00:28:02,766 --> 00:28:04,700
One day P'Phet would've found out anyway.

439
00:28:05,069 --> 00:28:06,358
Just...

440
00:28:06,681 --> 00:28:10,000
the way you told P'Phet was a bit nosy.

441
00:28:10,231 --> 00:28:10,976
But...

442
00:28:11,392 --> 00:28:15,422
it's okay. Haven't you heard?

443
00:28:15,422 --> 00:28:16,533
Everything happens for a reason.

444
00:28:16,764 --> 00:28:19,204
Everything happens for a reason.

445
00:28:19,204 --> 00:28:21,427
Uh, like master, like man.

446
00:28:21,427 --> 00:28:24,993
And... hens pecking kids on the elephant's back?

447
00:28:24,993 --> 00:28:26,095
Wait, wait.

448
00:28:26,372 --> 00:28:26,872
No.

449
00:28:27,411 --> 00:28:28,214
That's irrelevant.

450
00:28:28,214 --> 00:28:30,000
I just wanted to make you smile.

451
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:35,418
But...

452
00:28:36,249 --> 00:28:37,891
if you're feeling down,

453
00:28:38,122 --> 00:28:39,316
I think...

454
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:42,184
apologizing wouldn't hurt.

455
00:28:43,338 --> 00:28:44,511
Besides,

456
00:28:45,065 --> 00:28:46,287
he'll know that...

457
00:28:46,887 --> 00:28:48,559
...you actually care about him.

458
00:28:49,021 --> 00:28:50,000
Right?

459
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:54,800
huh?

460
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:57,566
Stop posing for five minutes and do something good.

461
00:28:57,769 --> 00:28:58,569
Come on.

462
00:28:58,569 --> 00:28:59,269
Let's go.

463
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:00,000
Where?

464
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:00,533
huh?

465
00:29:00,866 --> 00:29:01,774
Hurry.

466
00:29:01,774 --> 00:29:02,331
Right now?

467
00:29:02,331 --> 00:29:02,831
Right now.

468
00:29:03,066 --> 00:29:03,720
Seriously?

469
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:04,220
Yeah.

470
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:05,900
Hurry up.

471
00:29:40,166 --> 00:29:41,666
Guy, I want to...

472
00:29:41,866 --> 00:29:42,966
You don't have to apologize.

473
00:29:46,133 --> 00:29:47,288
One day...

474
00:29:47,981 --> 00:29:49,512
...P'Phet would've known anyway.

475
00:29:52,733 --> 00:29:53,686
Well...

476
00:29:53,686 --> 00:29:55,300
I should've told him from the start.

477
00:29:58,566 --> 00:30:00,000
But if you had,

478
00:30:00,533 --> 00:30:01,800
you wouldn't have been able to go, right?

479
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:05,329
Why?

480
00:30:06,114 --> 00:30:08,150
When it's me, there's always a problem.

481
00:30:09,258 --> 00:30:10,836
But when it's P'Ploy,

482
00:30:11,621 --> 00:30:12,686
nothing ever happens.

483
00:30:21,566 --> 00:30:22,633
Then?

484
00:30:23,972 --> 00:30:24,981
What are you going to do next?

485
00:30:30,666 --> 00:30:31,966
I'm going to sign the contract.

486
00:30:33,866 --> 00:30:34,629
You mean...

487
00:30:35,276 --> 00:30:36,866
...you're really quitting Likay?

488
00:30:37,066 --> 00:30:38,087
I'm not quitting.

489
00:30:39,195 --> 00:30:40,782
I just want to give it a try.

490
00:30:42,444 --> 00:30:44,730
This is another dream of mine too.

491
00:30:51,366 --> 00:30:52,645
Guy.

492
00:30:53,984 --> 00:30:54,986
I'm asking you seriously.

493
00:30:56,417 --> 00:30:58,292
How many times have you secretly auditioned?

494
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:00,956
A lot.

495
00:31:02,064 --> 00:31:03,537
So many that I almost gave up.

496
00:31:03,906 --> 00:31:06,184
I thought I'd never get to act in a series.

497
00:31:10,066 --> 00:31:12,272
Well, this time...

498
00:31:13,611 --> 00:31:15,478
...give it your all, man.

499
00:31:15,801 --> 00:31:17,057
Opportunities...

500
00:31:17,057 --> 00:31:18,836
...don't come by easily.

501
00:31:20,369 --> 00:31:22,111
As for the Petchprakai Troupe...

502
00:31:22,111 --> 00:31:23,555
...don't you worry about it.

503
00:31:23,832 --> 00:31:24,669
I'll be the one...

504
00:31:25,085 --> 00:31:26,375
...to look after P'Phet myself.

505
00:31:30,666 --> 00:31:31,466
You can rest easy.

506
00:31:38,333 --> 00:31:39,333
Thanks, man.

507
00:31:40,766 --> 00:31:41,566
Chill.

508
00:31:56,300 --> 00:31:57,333
Hey, Guy.

509
00:31:58,366 --> 00:32:00,533
I need some advice.

510
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,200
About what?

511
00:32:03,766 --> 00:32:04,566
Do you think...

512
00:32:05,966 --> 00:32:07,000
...what should I do...

513
00:32:07,533 --> 00:32:08,500
...to look like...

514
00:32:09,266 --> 00:32:11,066
...I have a future in Lynchee's eyes?

515
00:32:11,466 --> 00:32:12,333
Help me out here.

516
00:32:17,266 --> 00:32:18,466
Is she in university?

517
00:32:19,366 --> 00:32:20,166
Yeah, she is.

518
00:32:20,566 --> 00:32:21,766
Then you should study too.

519
00:32:22,700 --> 00:32:23,894
How else can you take care of her?

520
00:32:24,217 --> 00:32:24,733
Okay.

521
00:32:25,533 --> 00:32:26,835
Then I'll go and enroll.

522
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,400
Just like that?

523
00:32:28,666 --> 00:32:29,466
Hell yeah.

524
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:31,423
Opportunities...

525
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:33,923
...don't come by easily, like I told you.

526
00:32:34,570 --> 00:32:35,252
If you're going to do it,

527
00:32:35,252 --> 00:32:37,181
do it to the fullest.

528
00:32:37,181 --> 00:32:39,324
You too.

529
00:32:39,900 --> 00:32:41,200
Give it your all.

530
00:32:41,666 --> 00:32:42,766
And let's see...

531
00:32:43,266 --> 00:32:44,400
...between you and me...

532
00:32:45,333 --> 00:32:46,900
...who's going to reach the finish line first.

533
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:48,400
Okay.

534
00:32:55,066 --> 00:32:55,866
Yeah.

535
00:32:56,666 --> 00:32:57,466
Challenge accepted.

536
00:33:11,333 --> 00:33:12,933
I'm going to university.

537
00:33:13,566 --> 00:33:15,000
What on earth are you doing?

538
00:33:33,466 --> 00:33:34,700
I'm going to be a star.

539
00:33:47,700 --> 00:33:48,500
Let's go.

540
00:33:54,672 --> 00:33:55,718
Oh, it's low.

541
00:33:55,718 --> 00:33:56,484
Got it.

542
00:33:56,484 --> 00:33:57,396
Whoa, I got it!

543
00:33:59,151 --> 00:34:00,000
Whoa!

544
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,261
Boom!

545
00:34:02,508 --> 00:34:03,999
What a Pokdeng!

546
00:34:04,692 --> 00:34:05,598
Double!

547
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:26,302
Tor Prakai, please review the contract.

548
00:34:26,302 --> 00:34:27,835
And sign every page.

549
00:34:28,251 --> 00:34:30,533
If you have any questions, feel free to ask me.

550
00:34:33,533 --> 00:34:34,260
Wait.

551
00:34:34,860 --> 00:34:36,269
But how do I ask?

552
00:35:05,333 --> 00:35:06,333
What language is this?

553
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:07,933
Who could even read this?

554
00:35:10,666 --> 00:35:11,800
Need some help?

555
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:18,600
I thought you wouldn't show up.

556
00:35:19,533 --> 00:35:20,333
Why?

557
00:35:21,166 --> 00:35:21,870
Well...

558
00:35:22,424 --> 00:35:24,054
...your brother.

559
00:35:29,333 --> 00:35:30,533
If it's so great,

560
00:35:31,733 --> 00:35:33,500
if it's that good, then go live with him!

561
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:37,266
You don't want to be with Petchprakai anyway.

562
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:39,133
Are you kicking me out...

563
00:35:40,566 --> 00:35:42,366
...because if I don't perform Likay,

564
00:35:43,866 --> 00:35:45,766
I'm useless to you, right?

565
00:35:48,900 --> 00:35:50,000
Then I'm leaving.

566
00:35:52,733 --> 00:35:53,600
Guy! Guy!

567
00:36:01,066 --> 00:36:02,602
I'll prove to him...

568
00:36:02,833 --> 00:36:04,031
...that I can do it.

569
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:19,733
But for now...

570
00:36:19,733 --> 00:36:20,546
...can I borrow a pen?

571
00:36:20,823 --> 00:36:21,484
I forgot to bring one.

572
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:40,000
Ow!

573
00:36:40,133 --> 00:36:41,933
The fire just won't light.

574
00:36:42,333 --> 00:36:44,266
Where did Ping Pong Chae go?

575
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:46,600
Hey!

576
00:36:47,566 --> 00:36:48,500
What should I do?

577
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:51,200
Ow!

578
00:36:57,666 --> 00:36:59,366
Is it all my fault?

579
00:37:01,733 --> 00:37:04,300
Blaming others is easier than blaming yourself, right?

580
00:37:05,766 --> 00:37:06,881
I know...

581
00:37:07,712 --> 00:37:08,955
...that one day...

582
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,797
...you'll regret what you said.

583
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,300
Why not try using a fan?

584
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:25,400
Next time you light a fire,

585
00:37:27,533 --> 00:37:28,566
It'll make things easier.

586
00:37:31,733 --> 00:37:32,533
Thank you.

587
00:37:38,766 --> 00:37:40,400
(Ploy Ying) Look, P'Phet.
(Phet Tae) Ploy was right.

588
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:43,800
huh?

589
00:37:44,100 --> 00:37:44,933
Ploy was right.

590
00:37:46,133 --> 00:37:47,300
That I'd regret it.

591
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:50,800
And I really do regret it.

592
00:37:56,500 --> 00:37:58,366
I'm sorry for what I said.

593
00:38:04,966 --> 00:38:06,694
I'm sorry too.

594
00:38:07,756 --> 00:38:09,775
For not telling you about Guy.

595
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:11,330
I thought...

596
00:38:11,699 --> 00:38:14,673
...if Guy wanted you to know, he'd tell you.

597
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,200
I guess I'm not a good brother.

598
00:38:20,400 --> 00:38:21,666
That my siblings don't want to talk to me.

599
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:24,468
P'Phet.

600
00:38:24,653 --> 00:38:26,051
Don't think like that.

601
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:29,493
Sometimes...

602
00:38:29,493 --> 00:38:31,496
...the people we love the most...

603
00:38:31,912 --> 00:38:34,658
...are the hardest ones to talk to.

604
00:38:37,013 --> 00:38:38,982
They just don't want to hurt us.

605
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:42,032
But I know Guy isn't like that.

606
00:38:42,771 --> 00:38:43,928
He's stubborn.

607
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:47,400
If he's stubborn...

608
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,566
...he probably got it from you.

609
00:38:50,266 --> 00:38:51,066
Ow!

610
00:38:53,066 --> 00:38:54,000
What's wrong, Ploy?

611
00:39:00,166 --> 00:39:02,682
Is it the smoke? Does it sting?

612
00:39:04,206 --> 00:39:05,766
And here's another one.

613
00:39:06,459 --> 00:39:07,810
Wanting to go to Bangkok.

614
00:39:08,918 --> 00:39:11,473
If I let you go, I'd be worried sick.

615
00:39:13,089 --> 00:39:14,446
Feeling better?

616
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:21,811
Honestly,

617
00:39:22,227 --> 00:39:24,369
I haven't even replied to them yet.

618
00:39:24,784 --> 00:39:26,141
About what to do next.

619
00:39:26,557 --> 00:39:27,482
Do you think...

620
00:39:28,498 --> 00:39:30,245
...should I act in the series?

621
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,600
You still haven't replied?

622
00:39:33,733 --> 00:39:34,533
Mmm.

623
00:39:34,733 --> 00:39:36,666
They're starting the BL series first.

624
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:38,700
Mine hasn't started yet.

625
00:39:40,166 --> 00:39:41,300
What should I do?

626
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:46,089
I don't know. It's up to you.

627
00:39:46,089 --> 00:39:48,204
I don't want to decide for you.

628
00:39:48,573 --> 00:39:50,736
Whatever path you choose,

629
00:39:50,736 --> 00:39:52,069
you'll have me...

630
00:39:54,733 --> 00:39:56,256
...and Petchprakai...

631
00:39:56,718 --> 00:39:58,320
...by your side, always.

632
00:40:02,333 --> 00:40:03,266
Almost had a moment.

633
00:40:06,900 --> 00:40:10,133
Just don't find a new leading lady yet.

634
00:40:12,733 --> 00:40:14,387
Hey, the fire's lit!

635
00:40:14,387 --> 00:40:16,200
Grab the pot, hurry!

636
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:17,933
Took long enough.

637
00:40:21,366 --> 00:40:22,974
And if...

638
00:40:23,805 --> 00:40:26,279
...you really become a star...

639
00:40:27,572 --> 00:40:29,727
...don't forget to visit home often.

640
00:40:34,566 --> 00:40:35,366
Why?

641
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:39,866
Someone might miss you.

642
00:40:43,733 --> 00:40:46,485
If that person tells me directly...

643
00:40:47,547 --> 00:40:48,722
...without beating around the bush...

644
00:40:49,230 --> 00:40:50,253
...I promise...

645
00:40:50,253 --> 00:40:53,159
...I'll race back on my bike.

646
00:40:56,566 --> 00:40:57,933
I'll think about it.

647
00:40:58,700 --> 00:40:59,566
Mmm.

648
00:41:00,333 --> 00:41:01,900
Not thinking about it now.

649
00:41:07,733 --> 00:41:11,862
Hey, hold this for a sec. Keep fanning it.

650
00:41:11,862 --> 00:41:14,000
Is it boiling yet? Not yet. Help me fan it.

651
00:41:19,495 --> 00:41:22,633
I passed the final casting.
I've signed as an actor.

652
00:41:32,053 --> 00:41:34,428
Fabulous. Should I tell P'Phet?

653
00:41:34,428 --> 00:41:36,498
No need. He doesn't want to know.

654
00:41:40,566 --> 00:41:41,933
These two siblings...

655
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:44,766
Did Guy text you?

656
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:49,500
If you want to know, ask him yourself.

657
00:41:52,500 --> 00:41:53,300
Better not.

658
00:41:56,733 --> 00:41:58,900
Both of you are the same.

659
00:42:11,066 --> 00:42:11,966
How is it? Ready?

660
00:42:12,166 --> 00:42:12,966
Smells good.

661
00:42:13,266 --> 00:42:14,066
Oops.

662
00:42:14,266 --> 00:42:16,133
My cooking has improved.

663
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:18,333
But you lit the fire...

664
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:20,800
...and I did the seasoning.

665
00:42:21,466 --> 00:42:23,133
We wouldn't be eating if you hadn't come.

666
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:24,737
huh.

667
00:42:24,737 --> 00:42:26,866
A new kind of cold stew.

668
00:42:42,533 --> 00:42:43,333
Hey.

669
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:45,466
You forgot your bag.

670
00:42:47,333 --> 00:42:48,133
Thanks.

671
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:52,500
Have you told your brother?

672
00:42:56,533 --> 00:42:57,600
I told P'Ploy.

673
00:43:03,133 --> 00:43:04,066
As for P'Phet...

674
00:43:07,966 --> 00:43:08,766
...forget it.

675
00:43:09,333 --> 00:43:10,133
Oh.

676
00:43:13,100 --> 00:43:14,623
I'm done signing.

677
00:43:15,408 --> 00:43:16,585
I'd better head back.

678
00:43:17,509 --> 00:43:18,693
Thanks for today.

679
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:20,479
Wait, you.

680
00:43:20,479 --> 00:43:21,836
It's only noon.

681
00:43:22,205 --> 00:43:23,500
Where are you rushing off to?

682
00:43:24,166 --> 00:43:25,337
To get some food.

683
00:43:25,568 --> 00:43:26,764
I'm hungry.

684
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:27,990
Hey.

685
00:43:29,144 --> 00:43:30,504
I'm hungry too.

686
00:43:33,366 --> 00:43:35,100
Come eat with me.

687
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:40,565
Is this...

688
00:43:41,904 --> 00:43:43,485
...a request or what?

689
00:43:50,933 --> 00:43:51,966
I'm just telling you.

690
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,566
Because you're coming anyway.

691
00:44:11,366 --> 00:44:12,200
Weird, right?

692
00:44:12,966 --> 00:44:15,333
I've asked you to get in twice now.

693
00:44:16,500 --> 00:44:17,933
You've never said no.

694
00:44:19,166 --> 00:44:19,966
Why?

695
00:44:24,933 --> 00:44:25,633
I don't know.

696
00:44:26,372 --> 00:44:27,174
Figure it out yourself.

697
00:44:32,666 --> 00:44:33,574
Hey.

698
00:44:34,082 --> 00:44:35,242
Then...

699
00:44:36,305 --> 00:44:38,863
...crispy pork basil at the same place?

700
00:44:41,966 --> 00:44:43,200
Mmm, sure.

701
00:45:05,866 --> 00:45:07,466
Let's go.

702
00:45:28,440 --> 00:45:30,000
♪ We are ♪

703
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:31,584
♪ all alone ♪

704
00:45:31,861 --> 00:45:34,473
♪ and lonely ♪

705
00:45:35,581 --> 00:45:38,585
♪ But if by my side ♪

706
00:45:39,047 --> 00:45:41,647
♪ I have you ♪

707
00:45:42,386 --> 00:45:44,950
♪ You are my strength ♪

708
00:45:45,366 --> 00:45:48,802
♪ whenever we meet ♪

709
00:45:49,264 --> 00:45:52,780
♪ All I need is you ♪

710
00:45:53,472 --> 00:45:55,795
♪ alone ♪

711
00:45:57,457 --> 00:45:59,414
♪ My heart fears no pain ♪

712
00:46:00,476 --> 00:46:03,400
♪ You are my safe zone ♪

713
00:46:04,370 --> 00:46:08,402
♪ Giving me gentleness ♪

714
00:46:08,956 --> 00:46:12,868
♪ to each other ♪

715
00:46:19,466 --> 00:46:21,290
It must be Petchprakai's karma.

716
00:46:21,290 --> 00:46:23,566
That everyone we build up betrays us.

717
00:46:23,933 --> 00:46:25,727
You're actually using the word betrayal?

718
00:46:25,727 --> 00:46:27,766
Even after everything I've done for Petchprakai?

719
00:46:28,066 --> 00:46:30,696
Let me see it, your Likay troupe.

720
00:46:30,696 --> 00:46:32,018
It's not mine.

721
00:46:32,018 --> 00:46:32,866
It's my brother's.

722
00:46:33,300 --> 00:46:35,166
Have you messaged Guy yet?

723
00:46:35,566 --> 00:46:37,666
I want to focus on Petchprakai first.

724
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:40,650
Then you need to care more about those who are still here.

725
00:46:40,650 --> 00:46:44,856
I've realized what I must do most.

726
00:46:44,856 --> 00:46:47,869
It's to tell P'Phet directly that...

727
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:51,473
I like you, P'Phet.
